Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F762953016F3B8B8" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2206,2291,873,906]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F6DE953017B6B8B8" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[2338,2486,873,906]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF3C6A83F7A895C91683B883" box="[2132,2179,912,945]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">See</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F77395C91741B883" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2191,2369,912,945]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="967" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
. Most recent phylogenetic studies show that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F67795E11440B8EB" authorityName="Yoshiyuki" authorityYear="1971" box="[2443,2624,952,985]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pruinosus">M. pruinosus</taxonomicName>
as sister to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F77095BD1750BF33" authorityName="Maeda &amp; Matsumura" authorityYear="1998" box="[2188,2384,996,1025]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yanbarensis">M. yanbarensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F66695BD143FBF33" box="[2458,2623,996,1025]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="secundus">M. secundus</taxonomicName>
and more distantly related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F657925E143FBF1A" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[2475,2623,1031,1064]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
species group. Ancestral 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F67C9277143FBF7D" authorityName="Yoshiyuki" authorityYear="1971" box="[2432,2623,1070,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pruinosus">M. pruinosus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83F7D1920F16F1BF45" authorityName="Maeda &amp; Matsumura" authorityYear="1998" box="[2093,2289,1110,1143]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yanbarensis">M. yanbarensis</taxonomicName>
might have adapted to warm temperatures, with probable origin in 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF3C6A83F8059225168ABFAF" box="[2041,2186,1148,1181]" country="Botswana" name="South East" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">South-east</collectingRegion>
Asia. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
